In the Matter of MUNSON STEAMSHIP LINE, Debtor. In the Matter of The Appeals of HUNT, HILL & BETTS, Appellants, and Bennet, House & Couts, Appellants. Munson Line, Incorporated, Appellee. No. 192. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Dec. 26, 1939. Hunt, Hill & Betts, of New York City, pro se. Bennet, House & Couts, of New York City (William S. Bennet, Victor House, and Samuel H. Levinkind, all of New York City, of counsel), pro se. Lowell M. Birrell, of New York City (Lloyd C. Hartman, of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before SWAN, AUGUSTUS N. HAND, and CLARK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Orders affirmed.
